Package: debootstick
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, lvm2, kpartx, squashfs-tools, grub-efi-amd64-bin
Recommends: debootstrap, kvm, ovmf
Description: Generate a bootable live image from a filesystem tree
 debootstick is used to generate a bootable Ubuntu image from 
 an Ubuntu filesystem tree (such as one generated with debootstrap).
 This image should then be copied to a USB stick or disk. 

